text â€¹Interesting, relational functor \<^const>â€¹Transformation_Functorâ€º is (generally) stronger than
  the functional functor \<^const>â€¹Functional_Transformation_Functorâ€º.
  It is actually the combination of \<^const>â€¹Functional_Transformation_Functorâ€º and the

  \<^term>â€¹Ï†MapTree D K Vâ€º is not relationally functorial over \<^term>â€¹Vâ€º unless (as a suffcient condition)
  \<^term>â€¹Kâ€º is functional. Here is an example demonstrating this.
